    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Fuel System - Installation - Secondary Fuel
        Filter Element
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s07.4.7" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Secondary Fuel Filter Element</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new fuel filter element in fuel filter housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not add fuel to the fuel filter housing; this can add contaminants to
                    the fuel.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring on fuel filter cap.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, the fuel filter element must be installed in the fuel filter housing.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The engine will not run if the filter element is not installed. The installed filter element opens
                    a check valve in the center of the stand pipe, allowing fuel to flow.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install fuel filter cap and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_158.xml" xrefid="s07.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s07.t2"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
